# Modus 2.0 Project Rules

## Setup Requirements
- **Theme Wrapper**: All apps MUST be wrapped in <ModusWcThemeProvider> in main.tsx.
- **CSS Order**: Import @trimble-oss/moduswebcomponents/modus-wc-styles.css BEFORE Tailwind in index.css.
- **Icons**: Use the jsDelivr CDN for Modus icons: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@trimble-oss/modus-icons@1/dist/modus-outlined/fonts/modus-icons.woff2.

## Component Usage & Event Handling
- **Text Inputs**: Use <ModusWcTextInput>. Access values via e.detail?.target?.value.
- **Buttons**: Use <ModusWcButton> with the onButtonClick prop (NOT onClick).
- **Checkboxes**: Use <ModusWcCheckbox> with onInputChange.
- **Typography**: Always use the <ModusWcTypography> component for text.
- **Navbar Layout**: Use <ModusWcNavbar>.
  - Logo/Title: Prefer placing the logo and app title inside the <ModusWcNavbar> using slot="start".
  - Slots: Use slot="start", slot="center", or slot="end".
  - Theme Switch: The Theme Switch MUST go in slot="end".

## Design & Styling
- **Colors**: NEVER use hex codes. Use CSS variables: --modus-wc-color-base-page (background), --modus-wc-color-base-content (text), and --modus-wc-color-base-100 (cards).
- **Layout**: Use bordered={false} for cards by default.
- **Spacing**: Set --padding-card to 1rem and use var(--modus-wc-spacing-xl) for vertical card margins.
- **Buttons**: Default to tertiary style; only one primary button per page.